RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 4 4F Dirt CR: 46. Maiden Special Weight Purse 8500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOTSA LOU Rushed up to duel inside of rival through backside, outpaced by SHISH KABOB into the bend, rebid at the eighth pole while still inside of foe, kept finding to overtake at the sixteenth and hold sway. SHISH KABOB Dueled outside of rival through backside before moving to clear advantage into the turn, passed down the lane at the sixteenth pole, tried but could not find more. CLASSIC CALIFORNIA Stalked in the four path up the backside while being pressed upon by the rider all the way, finished up well in latter stages. BUFFUM'S BEAUTY Stayed in touch with leaders on the rail, outpaced on the turn, always outrun by better. MOBILEAGILEHOSTILE Lagged in behind the field early, commenced outside the quarter pole and circled four wide for a bid, ended up in the eight path into the stretch and moved only beyond fading foes. DUKE CITY KITTY Settled on the rail in behind up the backside, checked out of spot between rival and the rail into the turn, re-engaged when swung to the three path inside the quarter pole, came with a very mild bid but had nothing left. MISS MY MAMMA Moved in the two path while in the rear and never improved position. MAGIC HUSSAR Travelled three wide up the backstretch, never threatened when the running got going, moved to the rail for the stretch, still found little.

ENTRY.NAME: Buffum's Beauty
ENTRY.OWNER: Adams Patricia D and Sheldon Brenda
ENTRY.COMMENT: In touch rail, outpaced to turn, always outrun by better

ENTRY.NAME: Lotsa Lou
ENTRY.COMMENT: Dueled ins, outpaced bend, rebid 1/8 ins, kept finding

ENTRY.NAME: Mobileagilehostile
ENTRY.COMMENT: Lagged, circled 4w 1/4, 8p str, beyond tiring

ENTRY.NAME: Duke City Kitty
ENTRY.COMMENT: Rail backside, check out into turn, engage 3p 1/4, no left

ENTRY.COMMENT: 2w rear, never improved

ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w in back, rail stretch, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Shish Kabob

ENTRY.COMMENT: 4p stalking backside, always pressed on, finished up well

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER THAT HAVE STARTED AT THE 2023 RILLITO PARK MEET AND HAVE NOT FINISHED BETTER THAN THIRD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TELLER Tracked well off the lead along the rail, commenced move when switched to the three path outside the quarter pole, got fully cranked at the three-sixteenths pole, made the lead inside the eighth in the three path, drew off powerfully. BAD KARMA Sent and moved up the two path first time by, cleared to the rail into the first turn at the half mile pole, opened up a hefty advantage up the backside that was maintained to the three-sixteenths, was overtaken just inside the eighth by a steamrolling foe, had nothing left late. EMPEROR'S CHOICE Set up inside in the move by the grandstand while in touch of leader, conceded to foe and traveled a distant second up the backstretch, prompted by rider to move at the quarter pole and loomed with a chance two wide at the eighth pole, emptied out in the run through the stretch. OUTLAW BY NATURE Had no speed early and was well detached through the preliminary running, moved up in the three path at the quarter pole and progressed well but simply had too much to do and just missed out on show honors. TRIPDOWNMEMORYLANE Moved far off the pace in two path, was through at the five-sixteenths pole and was eased down to and through the wire.

ENTRY.NAME: Outlaw by Nature
ENTRY.COMMENT: No speed, move up 3p 1/4, too much to do, missed show honors

ENTRY.NAME: Tripdownmemorylane
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2w off pace, through at 5/16, eased down to and through wire

ENTRY.NAME: Teller
ENTRY.COMMENT: Rail, move 3p 1/4, cranked 3/16, led lane 3p, drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Emperor's Choice
ENTRY.COMMENT: Let leader get away, prompted 1/4, loom 2w 1/8, emptied

ENTRY.NAME: Bad Karma
ENTRY.COMMENT: Sent 2p, clear rail 1/2, opened up, overtaken 1/8, no left

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 6 4F Dirt CR: 74. Allowance Purse 9300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MARCH 25, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GENERAL THAYER Commenced in a fierce battle up the backstretch, moved to a narrow advantage around the turn, drifted a few paths off line into the stretch, tussled in a remaining line of three down the lane, outlasted all for victory. FIGHT ME Pressed early three wide and moved to duel into the turn, loomed boldly three wide at the eighth pole, grinded after the lead down the lane but was held at bay by the eventual winner. BRON AND THE BROW Dueled between runners up the backstretch, maintained in battle through the turn and to the eighth pole, fought lane, had no more late. SWITCH BACK Settled along the rail in behind the top trio, maintained position on the turn and never gained in the heat of the running. NUMMY NUM Stalked right off the leaders in the four path, stayed in same lane around the turn, never menaced. BUMPY CUP Brushed the outside of the gate hard out of the blocks then shot sharply towards the inside on the rail, lagged behind rest after the tumultuous beginning, swung to the six path for the turn, never gained.

ENTRY.NAME: Switch Back
ENTRY.COMMENT: Rail behind top trio, maintain turn, no gain

ENTRY.NAME: General Thayer
ENTRY.COMMENT: Fierce battle, narrow adv turn, tussle str, outlasted all

ENTRY.NAME: Nummy Num
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalk off leaders 4p, 4p turn, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Bron and the Brow
ENTRY.COMMENT: Duel between, maintain position to 1/8, fought btwn, no more

ENTRY.NAME: Fight Me
ENTRY.COMMENT: Press to duel 3w, loom 3w 1/8, grind lane, held at bay

ENTRY.NAME: Bumpy Cup
ENTRY.COMMENT: Brushed gate, sharply shot inside, lagged, 6p turn, no gain

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 7 4F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 8450. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JANUARY 1, 2023. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NORTH DAWN Cleared from outer draw to lead on the rail, maintained position through the turn before drifting to the three path at the eighth pole, repelled inside challenger down the lane and held sway. TOTHEMOONANDBACK Advanced from a slightly delayed break on the rail from the three-eighths to the quarter pole, continually gained on the inside of a rival through the stretch but was just outmatched by the winner. MULLIGAN Traveled off the rail in the second flight, dove to the rail on the turn, never menaced. SUE ETTAS GHOST Settled in rear, ran evenly on the turn despite being asked, showed mild late gain between rivals with a split run in the dying yards. SCAT ATTACK Broke on top but was outfooted by quicker outer rivals, continued to pursue inside, swung for clean air to the three path at the quarter pole, no match for field, tired lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Tothemoonandback
ENTRY.COMMENT: Adv from break 3/8 to 1/4, gain ins stretch, outmatched

ENTRY.NAME: Scat Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: Pursued inner, swung 3p, no match, tired lane

ENTRY.NAME: Sue Ettas Ghost
ENTRY.COMMENT: In rear, evenly turn, mild late gain split between

ENTRY.NAME: Mulligan
ENTRY.COMMENT: Off rail 2nd flight, moved to rail for turn, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: North Dawn
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Cleared to lead, drift 3p 1/8, held sway

RACE.RACE_TEXT: U of A RTIP S. RILLITO RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Stakes Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEARS OLD. No trials and no nomination. An entry fee of $250 due at the time of entry. First preference Arizona Bred, second preference by lifetime earnings. Maidens are least preferred. Same owner entries must prefer a horse at the time of ent ry. Weights: 3 years old . 124.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMA CARPE DIEM Flashed from the rail and led to the backside, left an opening on the rail for LILY PAD LAKE to come and duel at the seven-sixteenths, dueled between rivals from there to the turn, battled lane outside of a rival, roused to lead in the final stages. LILY PAD LAKE Missed the break, moved up at will to tuck in behind leaders into the first turn, advanced inside of an opening left by leading rival and picked up a three-horse duel to the eighth pole, fought with remaining rival through the lane inside and just missed at the line. MY MAN BIGGIE Broke to his face and lost many lengths on the field, forced to run well off the pace in the opening stages, split first pair of rivals outside the three-eighths pole while advancing well, moved between more rivals at the three-sixteenths, swung to the four path into the lane, flew home but had too much to do. HADLEES HONOR Joined the leader two wide into the first turn, moved a path out up the backside and vied three wide up the backstretch, remained in the fray to the eighth pole, gave way through the lane. JOHN'S KID Traveled in the four path into the first turn, maintained until being asked at the three-eighths to advance but never improved. SANTIAGO'S CAT Stalked four wide into the first turn juts off the leaders, let them progress up the backstretch and was content to track them, moved to the rail at the three-sixteenths to make a run but had nothing for the stretch. SUGAR SHANE Moved well of the rail into the first turn and remained the widest traveler throughout, never progressed.

ENTRY.NAME: Ima Carpe Diem
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Flashed, left opening, between to turn, battle, roused to lead

ENTRY.NAME: Lily Pad Lake
ENTRY.COMMENT: Missed break, tuck in, adv ins, duel to 1/8, fought, missed

ENTRY.NAME: My Man Biggie
ENTRY.COMMENT: Broke to face, off pace, split multiple, 4p lane, flew home

ENTRY.NAME: Hadlees Honor
ENTRY.COMMENT: Joined 2w lead, 3w backside, in fray to 1/8, gave way lane

ENTRY.NAME: John's Kid
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4p 1st, ask 3/8ths to advance, no improve

ENTRY.NAME: Sugar Shane
ENTRY.COMMENT: Well off rail 1st, widest throughout, no progression

ENTRY.NAME: Santiago's Cat
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalk 4w, let leaders go, move rail 3/16, nothing for stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 9 7 1/2F Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PEACE OF EKATI Settled in the four path off the pace, moved up four wide at the quarter pole for a bid, sustained rally around the bend, commenced a three wide battle down the stretch, kept finding for victory. QUEEN OF LOVE Stalked in the two path to the first turn, moved up at the five-sixteenths between horses, moved to the rail for a run at the quarter pole, shifted out a path into the stretch, battled between lane, could not find enough. BIG CITY BANE Tracked inside of runners into the first turn, advanced inside at the five-sixteenths, idled on the heels of rival around the turn, found a seam and moved through at the eighth pole, fought stretch, no match. NORTHERN QUEST Moved in the five path while in the rear throughout, asked at the quarter pole, moved to the six path down the lane, no menace. BREXTON Tracked the leaders in the three path, stalked three wide to the quarter pole in a line of four, backed out at the three-sixteenths pole, weakened through the lane. DR. TROUTMAN Missed the break a touch but rushed up to the lead the first time by, drifted well out to the five path in the move to the backstretch, wound up between rivals at the quarter pole when gaining rivals progressed with their challenges, shifted out to the eight path around the second turn, gave way down the stretch.

ENTRY.COMMENT: Tracked inner 1st, adv 5/16, idle turn, through 1/8, no match

ENTRY.NAME: Dr. Troutman

ENTRY.COMMENT: Miss break, rush to lead, 5p back, btwn 1/4, 8p turn, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Queen of Love
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2p 1st, move up 5/16, rail run 1/4, shift 2p str, not enough
